# Slurm Viewer
## Introduction
View the nodes in a slurm cluster and view the queue.

## Settings
placed in ~/.config/slurm_viewer/settings.json
```json
{
  "debug": "True",
  "server": "SERVER or NONE",
  "nodelist": ["List of nodes to view"],
  "node_columns": [
    "short_name",
    "gpu_tot",
    "gpu_alloc",
    "gpu_avail",
    "gpu_type",
    "gpu_mem",
    "cpu_tot",
    "cpu_alloc",
    "cpu_avail",
    "real_memory",
    "alloc_mem",
    "freemem"
  ],
  "queue_columns": [
    "nodelist",
    "user",
    "job_id",
    "command",
    "submit_time",
    "start_delay",
    "min_memory"
  ]
}
```
